cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Deep Learning (DL) techniques for text normalization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new general-purpose encoder based on causal convolutions, which is a DL technique, making cs.LG (Learning) another likely category. The paper also uses attention mechanisms, which are a common technique in DL, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. Additionally, the paper deals with improving the accuracy, number of parameters, and convergence time, which are optimization problems, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper also mentions the possibility of future improvements, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another possible category.
